The lock is engaged.
Katsuhito: "Beyond here is President Tsukeshiba's room."
Katsuhito: "If you have no business, please withdraw."
There's no need to go any further...

Toshie: "I'm happy you came to see Miss Karen, but she probably won't
meet with anyone..."

Toshie: "Even someone who has been with her for many years like
myself..."

Toshie: "Oh, does Lady Karen have a friend? That's quite rare, isn't
it?"

Yui: "I'm sorry. I wouldn't say we're close enough to be called
friends..."
Toshie: "Is that so..."
Toshie: "She can be quite willful... I apologize for that."
Yui: "No, it's not like that at all..."
Toshie: "Fufu, you're very kind, aren't you?"

Toshie: "You might find it hard to believe, but she used to be a shy
and delicate child."

Toshie: "Before transferring to Shoto Academy, she would water the
flowers here every day just like this."

Toshie: "She was a bit of a klutz, often spilling water on her
clothes, and it was just so adorable..."
Yui: "Saionji-san was...?"

Toshie: "After her father passed away, she transferred to Shoto
Academy and something inside her must have changed."

Toshie: "It was rare for her to make friends, but when she did, they
seemed to be the bad influence type..."

Toshie: "Whether it was because of that person's influence or not, she
seldom stayed at home and would go out night after night."

Toshie: "However, she seemed to be very dedicated to her club
activities."

Toshie: "Perhaps it was because her father was an athlete in his
student days... She loved her father dearly."

Toshie: "But now, due to circumstances at the academy, it seems she
can no longer participate in club activities and has been shut away in
her room."

Toshie: "I'm glad you came to visit, but I doubt she'll meet with
anyone..."
Toshie: "Even I, who have been with her for many years..."
